==Abstract==

This IIP defines the Partially Signed Transaction (PST) format for INTcoin, enabling multi-party signing, hardware wallet integration, and offline workflows. It adapts BIP 174 (PSBT) for ML-DSA-87 signatures.

==Motivation==

PST enables:
* Hardware wallet signing without full node
* Multi-party transaction construction
* Offline signing workflows
* CoinJoin-style privacy transactions

==Specification==

===Format===

<pre>
<magic> <global> <inputs> <outputs>

magic:  0x70 0x73 0x74 0xff 0x00 ("pst\xff\x00")
</pre>

===Global Fields===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Type !! Key !! Description
|-
| 0x00 || (none) || Unsigned transaction
|-
| 0x01 || (none) || Transaction version (if no unsigned tx)
|-
| 0xfb || (none) || Version number
|}

===Per-Input Fields===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Type !! Key !! Description
|-
| 0x00 || (none) || Non-witness UTXO
|-
| 0x01 || (none) || Witness UTXO
|-
| 0x02 || pubkey || Partial signature
|-
| 0x03 || (none) || Sighash type
|-
| 0x04 || (none) || Redeem script
|-
| 0x05 || (none) || Witness script
|-
| 0x06 || pubkey || BIP32 derivation
|-
| 0x07 || (none) || Final scriptSig
|-
| 0x08 || (none) || Final scriptWitness
|}

===Per-Output Fields===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Type !! Key !! Description
|-
| 0x00 || (none) || Redeem script
|-
| 0x01 || (none) || Witness script
|-
| 0x02 || pubkey || BIP32 derivation
|}

===Roles===

* '''Creator''': Creates PST from inputs/outputs
* '''Updater''': Adds UTXO and derivation info
* '''Signer''': Adds signatures
* '''Combiner''': Merges PSTs from multiple signers
* '''Finalizer''': Creates final scriptSig/scriptWitness
* '''Extractor''': Extracts signed transaction

===Serialization===

Key-value format:
<pre>
<key_len> <key_type> [key_data] <value_len> <value_data>
</pre>

Each map ends with 0x00 separator.

===ML-DSA-87 Signatures===

Partial signatures (type 0x02) contain:
* Key: ML-DSA-87 public key (2592 bytes)
* Value: ML-DSA-87 signature (4627 bytes)

===Base64 Encoding===

PSTs are transmitted as Base64, starting with "cHN0" (base64 of "pst").

